commit.message:
Several cmake fixes

- GNUInstallDirs has to be moved up, otherwise CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR is
empty when generating liborigin.pc
- corrected liborigin.pc var names (they are case sensitive)
- made opj2dat optional

TODO: add option to toggle build/install of static libs

Signed-off-by: Andrew Ammerlaan <andrewammerlaan@gentoo.org>

commit.message: Build only static library when it is built as a subproject.

Fix Installtion targets and directories.

Don't Install anything if liborigin is built as a subproject.
Replace empty quotation marks  by string()

[PATCH 3/3] readProjectTree: provide root node to append to

append_child() is not supposed to work on an empty tree,
and I couldn't find any initialization before its use.
All inserted nodes seemed to end up below tree_node::feet
(or something) and were not cleaned up by the destructor.

Using insert() to create a dummy node for others to be
children of fixes the leak.

provided by Ivan Krylov (Ropj)

[PATCH 2/3] fix bugs found by UBSan

 - check values before casting to enum Attach
 - default-initialize sensitive struct elements

provided by Ivan Krylov (Ropj)

[PATCH 1/3] do not output to standard streams (cout, cerr) by default

it might be better to hide all such usage behind #ifdefs,
since the streams might not belong to the shared library
